Key Match Events: Baghdad Bounedjah put Algeria in front with a clinical finish after just 18 minutes.
Bounedjah's subsequent overhead kick was disallowed for offside after a VAR review.
Mabululu equalized for Angola in the 65th minute by converting a penalty after his initial spot-kick hit the underside of the bar.
Post-Match Reflections: Angola's Mabululu celebrated his equaliser against Algeria, salvaging a point for his team.
Algeria's frustration continued as they failed to win a game in the Africa Cup of Nations.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Algeria became increasingly frustrated as they failed to create further chances to trouble Angola.
Angola drew level in the 65th minute when Mabululu was brought down by Nabil Bentaleb in the box.
